body.description: Innovation. Suck on that! It’s the best thing to happen to feeding since nipples. The revolutionary air-free feeding design of our Nursh Silicone Pouch Bottle features a 100% silicone pouch that collapses as your little one drinks, squeezing out the nasty gas-inducing air that causes colic. No straws, vents or valves here—so it’s a snap to clean and assemble. The silicone design can even be boiled, sterilized, and frozen, making it a truly versatile baby bottle option. Each of the silicone bottles in this set are also dishwasher safe for quick and easy cleaning that makes taking care of them a snap. These 8-oz infant bottles include stage 2 medium flow nipples that are perfect for babies ready for a faster flow of milk or formula. These medium flow nipples are also designed to mimic mom to ensure your baby stays comfortable and at ease as they drink from their new silicone baby bottles. Boon's Nursh collection is perfect for new moms. Explore more of the collection to discover storage lids, buns, additional pouches, and more!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 23, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I was so excited to get these and they are perfect!
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. My baby boy just turned 4 months and has been pretty much refusing to take his tommee tippee anti-colic bottles because I only had size 1 nipples for them an he’s also teething which has been a horrible mix! He would take forever to finish a bottle and get so frustrated.. I know now it was a big mistake not to be prepared with size 2 lol but me and my fiancé have also grown so tired of washing all those parts every night, they worked really good for us other wise like helping with gassiness an etc.. but it’s been time for a change. I’ve done a lot of looking an research for something new and fell in love with the reviews and the adorable looks of these! And my baby loves them, it only takes him around 10-15mins tops to finish his bottle and his latch is great on it. they are so easy to clean an sanitize. I bought quite a few so I could have some for at home an always in my diaper bag which works great for us! The color difference in the dark grey and white is also perfect too which I seen most reviews say that they were too similar and the packaging they arrived in was also in great condition unlike some reviews. I’ve never had a leak issue because I make sure the bottle is put together correctly which is really easy! I love these bottles and definitely recommend, I hype them up to everyone. :) also for anyone wondering about the pacifiers, I ordered them off of Amazon also and they are literally the best! They are super light weight and stay in baby’s mouth all night, have a whole bunch of cute colors an sizes. and they’re the only paci on Amazon with just a lil under 20,000 5 star reviews! I also recommend them to everyone and it’s the first gift I’ll buy for anyone expecting or in need of a paci that actually works well. 4 people I know that I recommend them to already went and bought them and it’s the only ones their baby’s will use and they love them to. They are called Tommee Tippee Ultralights!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy to clean with no small parts!
reviews.reviewText: I love these bottles! I love that there’s not a lot of small parts that need to be scrubbed especially when tired & trying to be quick. Fairly easy to assemble, you just have to make sure everything is put together correctly or it could leak. The numbers can be hard to read especially if you’re sleepy but at the right angle you can see them. One of the inserts that holds the milk seems to be a little misshapen because we have to adjust it when we place it in the shell every time and the others we don’t, so we just have to remember that. Otherwise, we love these bottles & love that they come in many different colors!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My favorite bottles on the market
reviews.reviewText: I love the Boon Nursh bottles. They come in 4 oz and 8 oz options. The silicone insert collapses in on itself as baby drinks so that there is no excess air. One thing to keep in mind is if you are making an 8 oz bottle, there is not a lot of room for formula, but if you gently tap the bottle as you are adding, it will settle and not overflow. Also, make sure the lip of the silicone insert is seated properly, or the lid won’t screw on correctly and it’ll leak! But pop it back into place and all will be well. Not a ton of parts to clean and all dishwasher safe for easy cleanup. No weird creases or crevices to worry about either. I’ll be excited to try their other products in the future! (Colors are super adorable as well and do look like their packaging)
